## PRIMARY OBJECTIVE

> **Rules govern agents. Agents enforce rules. Community evolves rules.**
> **NEVER write manual logic if a Tool (MCP) or Agent exists.**
> **CHALLENGE before EXECUTE. Process before code.**
> **DRY-RUN FIRST. Always.**

## ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (MANDATORY)

> **Every message follows:** INTAKE -> CHALLENGE -> PLAN -> GATE -> EXECUTE -> VERIFY -> LEARN
> **Full spec:** `.guarani/orchestration/PIPELINE.md`

| Complexity | Pipeline Depth | Min Thoughts |
|------------|---------------|---------------|
| TRIVIAL | Skip to Execute | 0 |
| SIMPLE | Intake + Plan + Execute | 0 |
| MODERATE | Full pipeline, questions mandatory | 3 |
| COMPLEX | Full pipeline + Sequential Thinking | 5 |
| CRITICAL | Full pipeline + user approval | 7 |

## CORE DIRECTIVES

1. **CHALLENGE** έΑΦ Question, detect contradictions, ask for evidence.
2. **ONE THING** έΑΦ Each agent does ONE thing. Each module solves ONE problem.
3. **ZERO DEPS** έΑΦ Agents use only Node/Bun stdlib. No framework dependencies.
4. **DRY-RUN FIRST** έΑΦ Every agent SHALL support `--dry` before `--exec`.
5. **REGISTRY** έΑΦ No agent runs without `agents/registry/agents.json` entry.
6. **COST** έΑΦ AI calls use `packages/shared/src/llm-provider.ts`. Cost tracked.
7. **SHARED** έΑΦ Reusable code goes in `packages/shared/`. Zero duplication.
8. **COMMIT** έΑΦ Conventional commits every 30-60min.
9. **SCOPE** έΑΦ Do ONLY what was asked. ASK before creating new features.
10. **TEACH** έΑΦ Explain WHY, not just WHAT. Question bad ideas.
11. **EDIT SIZE** έΑΦ Max 80 lines per write_to_file/edit call.
12. **PROTECTED** έΑΦ Never edit protected surfaces without explicit user approval + proof.
13. **CODEX** έΑΦ Use Codex for diff-heavy, audit, and mechanical work.
14. **HUMAN LOOP** έΑΦ For ambiguous decisions, ask before acting.
15. **PROPAGATE** έΑΦ Kernel governance/workflow changes are not complete until `bun run governance:sync:exec` passes and `bun run governance:check` returns 0 drift.
16. **FOCUS** έΑΦ Do NOT reinvent what exists (generic scanners, linters, dep auditors). EGOS's moat is governance-as-code, Brazilian compliance, and orchestration. Before creating any new agent, search existing marketplaces (OpenClaw, aregistry.ai, Composio, npm). If user proposes new scope, acknowledge it, log to TASKS.md backlog, but REMIND them of current mission focus.
17. **REAL TESTS** έΑΦ No capability is "validated" by string-matching grep. Every shared module MUST have `bun test` coverage with real data. A compliance score without behavioral tests is paperwork, not proof.
18. **NO CIRCULAR VALIDATION** έΑΦ Agents that check for their own outputs are not tests. Validation requires external confrontation: real PII, adversarial prompts, actual API calls, or user-verified results.
19. **VERCEL CLI** έΑΦ When access exists, Vercel CLI may be used to inspect deployments, manage env vars, and trigger redeploys, but only with explicit human approval for the concrete action.
20. **SIGNATURE** έΑΦ Every operational message MUST end with the signature footer defined in `.guarani/standards/AGENT_MESSAGE_SIGNATURE_CONTRACT.md` (agent id, session id, mode, source env, UTC timestamp).

